The paper deals with logic programming and answer set semantics, which are topics related to artificial intelligence and logic. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses declarative approaches and transformations to logic programs, which are topics related to logic and databases, making cs.LO and cs.DB likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with preferences and conflicts, which are topics related to constraint satisfaction and computational complexity, making cs.PL and cs.CC possible sub-categories.
